<div class="body" id="fhbody-173659192">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-173659192" class="p">
			
		 	
				An anonymous reader shared <a href="https://apnews.com/article/pope-ai-artificial-intelligence-cisco-microsoft-ibm-79b279570b2e7a2d945c452852a19657">this report from the Associated Press</a>:

<i>Tech giant Cisco Systems on Wednesday joined Microsoft and IBM in signing onto a Vatican-sponsored pledge to ensure artificial intelligence is developed and used ethically and to benefit the common good...   The pledge outlines key pillars of ethical and responsible use of AI. It emphasizes that AI systems must be designed, used and regulated to serve and protect the dignity of all human beings, without discrimination, and their environments. It highlights principles of transparency, inclusion, responsibility, impartiality and security as necessary to guide all AI developments.<br> <br>

The document was unveiled and signed at a Vatican conference on Feb. 28, 2020... Pope Francis has called for an <a href="https://apnews.com/article/vatican-pope-ai-artificial-intelligence-9805fec11681adbf88d3a7c73bdf47de">international treaty to ensure AI is developed and used ethically</a>, devoting his annual peace message this year to the topic.</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
